milestones.description: Chris Old has broken the record for most ducks (2) in ODIs for ENG, going past Graham Roope's 1
Chris Old has become the top wicket-taker for ENG in ODIs with 21 wickets, going past Geoff Arnold's 18
Dennis Lillee has become the top wicket-taker for AUS in ODIs with 12 wickets, going past Mallett's 11
This is the lowest match aggregate (187) involving teams England & Australia in ODIs
Chris Old has become the highest wicket-taker in ODIs with 21 wickets, going past Geoff Arnold's 18
Greg Chappell has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (11) for AUS, going past Ian Chappell
Constant has broken the record for officiating the most ODIs (7) as an umpire, going past Dickie Bird
Geoff Arnold and Peter Lever's 20-run partnership is ENG's highest for the 10th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 18 between John Snow and Geoff Arnold
Doug Walters and Gary Gilmour's 55-run partnership is AUS's highest for the 7th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 48 between Ross Edwards and Max Walker
